		<description><![CDATA[I have updated my sidebar podcast links. Some of the links had changed, some podcasts were added, some have regrettably faded. I would love nothing more than to re-link to some that have disappeared. Theory of Everything, smallWORLD, The Seanachai and RU Sirius are at the top of that list; I truly miss them all [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I have updated my sidebar podcast links.  Some of the links had changed, some podcasts were added, some have regrettably faded.  </p>
<p>I would love nothing more than to re-link to some that have disappeared.  Theory of Everything, smallWORLD, The Seanachai and RU Sirius are at the top of that list; I truly miss them all and hope they return someday.  </p>
<p>As for those I&#8217;ve added, I&#8217;ll be the first to admit that they are almost all podcasts of radio programs.  I haven&#8217;t kept up with too many new indy podcasts and I feel bad that I haven&#8217;t.  The fact of the matter is, it takes a lot of time to search new ones out, and I&#8217;ve kissed a lot of frogs doing so.   If you suspect there are any independent podcasts I should listen and link to, let me know.  I&#8217;ll listen to anything once.  If it&#8217;s halfway intelligent and has good sound, I might even listen to it all the way through.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
